{"title_page": "Kelapur", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=April 2017}}\n{{Unreferenced|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Kelapur\n| native_name             = \n| native_name_lang        = \n| other_name              = \n| nickname                = \n| settlement_type         = city\n| image_skyline           = \n| image_alt               = \n| image_caption           = \n| pushpin_map             = India Maharashtra\n| pushpin_label_position  = right\n| pushpin_map_alt         = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in Maharashtra, India\n| coordinates             = {{coord|20.0167|N|78.5333|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = {{flag|India}}\n| subdivision_type1       = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Maharashtra]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Yavatmal district|Yavatmal]]\n| established_title       = <!-- Established -->\n| established_date        = \n| founder                 = \n| named_for               = \n| government_type         = \n| governing_body          = \n| unit_pref               = Metric\n| area_footnotes          = \n| area_rank               = \n| area_total_km2          = \n| elevation_footnotes     = \n| elevation_m             = 240\n| population_total        = \n| population_as_of        = 2001\n| population_rank         = \n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_demonym      = \n| population_footnotes    = \n| demographics_type1      = Languages\n| demographics1_title1    = Official\n| demographics1_info1     = [[Marathi language|Marathi]]\n| timezone1               = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1             = +5:30\n| postal_code_type        = <!-- [[Postal Index Number|PIN]] -->\n| postal_code             = \n| registration_plate      = \n| website                 = \n| footnotes               = \n}}\n'''Kelapur''' (also called as '''Pandharkawda''') is a [[census town]], [[tehsil]] and subdivision of [[Yavatmal district]]  in the state of [[Maharashtra]], [[India]].\n\nIt is located on [[Srinagar]] - [[Nagpur]] - [[Hyderabad, Andhra Pradesh|Hyderabad]] - [[Bangalore]] - [[Kanyakumari (town)|Kanyakumari]] [[National Highway 44 (India)|National Highway 44]].\n\nIt is famous for the Jagadamba Bhavani Mata Temple. The temple is oldest one in this region and the devotee come from not only Maharashtra State but also from states like [[Telangana]]. This Bhavani Mata is considered the Tuljapur Bhavani Mata with different name. \nThe navratra festival at this place is just excellent.\n\n\n\n\n\nThe most popular person in the city of Pandharkawada is Mr. Sakib Majeed Sheikh, in Yavatmala district the only one person who wrote 300K Like  , on tik tok.\n\nTik tok id- @sakibsheikh3\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n\n{{Geographic Location\n|Centre    = Kelapur\n|North     = \n|Northeast = [[Hinganghat]]([[Wardha district]])\n|East      = [[Wani, Maharashtra]]\n|Southeast = \n|South     = [[Adilabad]], ([[Andhra Pradesh State]])\n|Southwest = \n|West      = [[Parwa]]\n|Northwest = [[Ghatanji]]\n}}\n\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Yavatmal district]]\n[[Category:Talukas in Maharashtra]]\n\n{{Yavatmal-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=April 2017}}\n{{Unreferenced|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Kelapur\n| native_name             = \n| native_name_lang        = \n| other_name              = \n| nickname                = \n| settlement_type         = city\n| image_skyline           = \n| image_alt               = \n| image_caption           = \n| pushpin_map             = India Maharashtra\n| pushpin_label_position  = right\n| pushpin_map_alt         = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in Maharashtra, India\n| coordinates             = {{coord|20.0167|N|78.5333|