l at this place is just excellent.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n\n{{Geographic Location\n|Centre    = Kelapur\n|North     = \n|Northeast = [[Hinganghat]]([[Wardha district]])\n|East      = [[Wani, Maharashtra]]\n|Southeast = \n|South     = [[Adilabad]], ([[Andhra Pradesh State]])\n|Southwest = \n|West      = [[Parwa]]\n|Northwest = [[Ghatanji]]\n}}\n\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Yavatmal district]]\n[[Category:Talukas in Maharashtra]]\n\n{{Yavatmal-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "103.108.75.26", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(pandharkawada famous person)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kelapur"}
{"title_page": "List of equipment of the Indian Army", "text_new": "{{more citations needed|date=January 2014}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=April 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2013}}\n\nThis is a list of some of the modern and historical '''equipment used by the [[Indian Army]]'''. Most of the army equipment is of foreign design and produced under licence in India but efforts are on to progressively design and manufacture equipment locally. The 41 [[Indian Ordnance Factories]] under control of [[Ordnance Factories Board]] manufacture most of the Army equipment like [[small arms]], [[ammunition]], [[combat vehicle]]s, [[artillery]], [[tank]]s etc.\n\n==Infantry weapons==\n\n===Small Arms===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|+\n|-\n! style=\"width:15%;\" | Name\n! style=\"width:10%;\" | Weapon\n! style=\"width:15%;\" | Type\n! style=\"width:5%;\" | Caliber\n! style=\"width:10%;\" | Origin\n! Notes\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" |Handguns\n|-\n|[[Pistol Auto 9mm 1A]]\n|[[File:Pistol Auto 9 mm 1A - Kolkata 2012-01-23 8779.JPG|[[Pistol Auto 9mm 1A]]|150px]]||[[Semi-automatic pistol]]||[[9mm Parabellum|9\u00d719mm Parabellum]]||{{CAN}}<br>{{IND}}||'''Status: In service.''' Standard side-arm of the Indian Army, manufactured under license.\n|-\n|[[Glock 17]]\n|[[File:Glock17.jpg|Glock 17|150px]]||[[Semi-automatic pistol]]||[[9mm Parabellum|9\u00d719mm Parabellum]]||{{AUT}}||'''Status: In service.''' Standard Special Forces pistol.\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" |Shotgun\n|-\n|[[Franchi SPAS-15]]\n|[[File:SPAS15.jpg|Franchi SPAS-15 Combat Shotgun|150px]]||[[Combat Shotgun]]|| 18.5 x 76&nbsp;mm NATO ||{{ITA}}||'''Status: In service.''' Used by special forces, which includes NSG.\n|-\n|[[OFB pump action Shotgun]]\n|[[File:6--sa12pagun.jpg|150px]]\n|[[pump action]]\n|[[12-gauge shotgun]]\n|{{IND}}\n|'''Status:In Service'''\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" |SMGs\n|-\n|[[Sterling submachine gun|SAF Carbine 2A1]]\n|[[File:Sterling SMG.JPG|[[SAF Carbine 2A1]]|150px]]||[[Submachine gun]]||[[9mm Parabellum|9\u00d719mm Parabellum]]||{{IND}}<br>{{GBR}}||'''Status: In service/will be Replaced.''' [[submachine gun|SAF Carbine 1A]]. To be replaced by the [[Modern Sub Machine Carbine|MSMC]].\n|-\n|[[Uzi#Military variants|Micro-Uzi]]\n|[[File:Uzi of the israeli armed forces.jpg|Micro-Uzi|150px]]||[[Submachine gun]]||[[9\u00d719mm Parabellum]]||{{ISR}}||'''Status: In service.''' For use by Special Forces. Micro-Uzi variant used.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bharat-rakshak.com/LAND-FORCES/Army/Galleries/50-5/0548.jpg |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-11-11 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121010190951/http://www.bharat-rakshak.com/LAND-FORCES/Army/Galleries/50-5/0548.jpg |archivedate=10 October 2012 |df=dmy-all }}?</ref>\n|-\n|[[Heckler & Koch MP5]]\n|[[File:Heckler & Koch MP5-1.jpg|MP5 Submachine Gun|150px]]||[[Submachine gun]]||[[9\u00d719mm Parabellum]]||{{GER}}||'''Status: In service.''' Used by Indian Army Special Forces\n|-\n|[[Br\u00fcgger & Thomet MP9]]\n|[[File:B&T MP9 SMG.JPG|MP9 machine pistol|150px]]||[[Machine pistol]]||[[9\u00d719mm Parabellum]]||{{CHE}}||'''Status: In service.''' Used by [[Ghatak Force|Ghatak Platoon]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2012/20121112/main4.htm|title=The Tribune, Chandigarh, India - Main News|website=www.tribuneindia.com|access-date=2016-10-27}}</ref>\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" |Assault Rifles\n|-\n|[[Steyr AUG]]\n|[[File:Steyr-AUG.jpeg|150px]]\n|[[Assault Rifle|Assault Rifle/Sub Machine Gun]]\n|[[5.56\u00d745mm NATO]] and [[9\u00d719mm Parabellum]](SMG Variant)\n|{{AUT}}\n|'''Status: In service.''' Used by special forces in small numbers.\n|-\n|[[FN SCAR]]\n|[[File:Scar L Standard.jpg|150px]]\n|[[Assault rifle]]\n|[[5.56\u00d745mm NATO]] and [[7.62\u00d751mm NATO|7.62x51mm NATO]]\n|{{BEL}}\n|'''Status: In service.''' Used by special forces including NSG, Para SF, MARCOS and SFF.\n|-\n||[[IMI Galil|IMI GALIL]]\n|[[File:Imfdb galil.jpg|150px]]\n|[[Assault rifle]]\n|[[5.56\u00d745mm