rorists, Pakistan Army on LoC|date=December 11, 2019|website=[[Asian News International]]|via=[[The Economic Times]]|language=en|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[CAR 816|Caracal International CAR 816]]\n|[[File:CAR 816.jpg|CAR 816|150px]]\n|[[Carbine]]\n|[[5.56\u00d745mm NATO]]\n|{{UAE}}\n|'''Status: On Order.'''\nOrder placed for 94,000 units of CAR 816 carbine.\n|-\n|[[T91 assault rifle]]\n|[[File:T91 assault rifle.jpg|150px]]\n|[[Assault rifle]]\n|[[5.56\u00d745mm NATO]]\n|{{TWN}}\n|'''Status: In Service.''' 1000+ unit of this rifle were brought\n|-\n|[[M16 rifle]]\n|[[File:M16a1m16a2m4m16a45wi.jpg|frameless|146x146px]]\n|[[Assault rifle]]\n|[[5.56\u00d745mm NATO]]\n|{{USA}}\n|'''Status: In service.''' Used by special forces\n|-\n|[[M4 carbine|M4A1 Carbine]]\n|[[File:PEO M4 Carbine RAS M68 CCO.jpg|M4A1 Assault Rifle|150px]]||[[Assault rifle]]||[[5.56\u00d745mm NATO]]||{{USA}}||'''Status: In service.''' Used by special forces, including PARA SF and Ghatak SF and MARCOS.\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" |Sniper rifles\n|-\n|[[Steyr SSG 69]]\n|[[File:Steyr SSG 69.jpg|Sniper Rifle|150px]]||[[Sniper rifle]]|| 7.62\u00d751mm NATO ||{{AUT}}||'''Status: In service.''' Standard bolt-action sniper rifle.\n|-\n|[[Mauser|Mauser SP66]]\n|[[File:Mauser sp66.JPG|Sniper Rifle|150px]]||[[Sniper rifle]]|| 7.62\u00d751mm NATO ||{{GER}}||'''Status: In service.''' Standard bolt-action sniper rifle.\n|-\n|[[SIG Sauer SSG 3000]]\n|[[File:SIG Sauer SSG 3000.jpg|Sniper Rifle|150px]]||[[Sniper rifle]]|| 7.62\u00d751mm NATO ||{{GER}}||'''Status: In service.''' Standard bolt-action sniper rifle.\n|-\n|[[Dragunov Sniper Rifle|Dragunov SVD]]\n|[[File:SVD Dragunov.jpg|Dargunov Sniper Rifle|150px]]||[[Sniper rifle]]||[[7.62\u00d754mmR]]||{{USSR}}<br>{{IND}}||'''Status: In service.''' Standard Designated Marksman rifle(DMR). To be replaced by a 7.62mm NATO DMR under the Army modernisation plan.<ref name=\"ndtv.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ndtv.com/india-news/re-arming-the-indian-armys-troops-with-l