dary weapon on T-72 and T-90 tanks. \n|-\n|[[KPV heavy machine gun|KPV]]\n|[[File:ZPU-1 in Iraq, 2003.JPEG|KPV heavy machine gun|150px]]||[[Heavy machine gun]]||14.5\u00d7114&nbsp;mm||{{USSR}}||'''Status: In service.''' Manufactured at Ordnance Factory Tiruchirappalli, used in small numbers.\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" |Indigenous Weapons\n|-\n|[[Vidhwansak]]\n|\n|[[Anti-materiel rifle]]||12.7\u00d7108mm, 20x82mm||{{IND}}||'''Status: In service.'''\n|-\n|[[INSAS|1B1 INSAS]]\n|[[File:INSAS Black.JPG|INSAS 1B1 Assault Rifle|150px]]||[[Assault rifle]]||[[5.56\u00d745mm NATO]]||{{IND}}||'''Status: In service/ To be replaced'''. Standard assault rifle of the Indian Army. To be replaced by [[AK-203]]\n|-\n|[[INSAS rifle#Variant & Developments|INSAS LMG]]\n|[[File:INSAS-LMG.jpg|INSAS LMG|150px]]||[[Light machine gun]]||[[5.56\u00d745mm NATO]]||{{IND}}||'''Status: In service(To be phased Out)'''  . Standard Squad Automatic Weapon (SAW) of the Indian Army. Light machine gun derivative of the INSAS assault rifle. Contract signed in 2020 to replace a large amount INSAS LMG with [[IMI Negev]]\n|-\n|[[Bren light machine gun|GUN MACHINE 7.62MM IA]]\n|[[File:Keeping Watch.jpg|Machinegun 7.62 MM IA|150px]]\n|[[Light machine gun|Light machine Gun]]\n|[[7.62\u00d751mm NATO|7.62 x 51 mm NATO]]\n|{{flag|India|3}}\n|'''Status: In Service (Being Phased out)''' Principal LMG for the Army, variant of British Bren Gun and Czech ZB 26, re chambered to NATO round. To be replaced by [[IMI Negev]] as per contract signed in 2020\n|}\n\n===Explosives, Rockets, and Mortars===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Name \n!Image\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Type \n! style=\"width:5%;\"| Quantity \n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Origin \n! Notes\n|-\n| Grenade 36mm \n| ||[[Hand Grenade]] ||  || {{Flagu|India}} || Fragmentation grenade which can be hand-thrown or rifle-launched from 1A SLR.\n|-\n| Multi Mode Grenade Shivalik \n|||[[Hand grenade]] || 1.8 million<ref>{{cite web|url=ht