 recoilless rifle.jpg|none|thumb]]||[[Recoilless rifle]] (84mm) || || {{IND}}<br>{{SWE}} ||Carl Gustav Recoilless Rifle produced by OFB.\n|-\n| [[Carl Gustav recoilless rifle|RCL Mk III]] || [[Recoilless rifle]] (84mm) || || {{IND}}<br>{{SWE}} ||Lighter, updated version of the RCL Mk II produced by OFB.\n|-\n| [[M40 recoilless rifle|106mm M-40A1]] \n|[[File:Land Rover Series 2A SWB with 106mm M40A2 recoilless rifle (5636779829).jpg|none|thumb]]||[[Recoilless rifle]] || 13000+ || {{USA}} ||\n|-\n|[[B-300|B-300 Shipon]]\n|[[File:Shipon001.jpg|none|thumb]]\n|[[RPO-A Shmel|Rocket Launcher]] ||\n|{{ISR}}\n|For use by Special Forces. Specially Marcos and Para(SF).\n|-\n| [[RPO-A Shmel]] \n|[[File:RPO-A missile and launcher.jpg|none|thumb]]||[[Rocket Launcher]] || || {{Flagu|Russia}} ||\n|-\n| [[C90-CR (M3)]] \n|[[File:C-90.jpg|none|thumb]]||[[Rocket Launcher]] || || {{flag|Spain}}|| In use with the infantry units. [[C90-CR (M3)|C-90-CR-RB (M3)]] variant only.\n|-\n| [[2-inch mortar|OFB E1 51mm]] \n|||[[Mortar (weapon)|Mortar]] || || {{IND}} ||Used by assault sections of infantry formations.\n|-\n| OFB E1 81mm<hr>[[L16 81mm mortar]] \n|[[File:81mmMORT L16.png|none|thumb]]||[[Mortar (weapon)|Mortar]] || 5000+ || {{Flagu|India}} ||Used by mortar platoons of infantry formations.\n|-\n|[[OFB E1 120mm]] \n|||[[Mortar (weapon)|Mortar]] || || {{IND}} ||\n|}\n\n==Vehicles==\n\n===Utility and miscellaneous===\n{{Expand list|date=December 2009}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:90%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Name \n!Image\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Type \n! style=\"width:5%;\"| Quantity \n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Origin \n! Notes\n|-\n|[[Royal Enfield Bullet]] 350/500\n|[[File:Modified royal enfield.jpg|frameless|220x220px]]\n|[[Motorcycle]]\n|\n|{{IND}}\n|Used by Corps of Military police and Acrobatic team\n|-\n|[[Hindustan Ambassador]]\n|[[File:Hindustan Ambassador Nova, New Delhi Secretariat.jpg|frameless|220x220px]]\n|[[Staff car]]\n|\n|{{IND}}\n|Ambassador is assigned to