5] (PDF), [[Flightglobal.com]]</ref>\n!Comment\n|-\n! style=\"align: center; background: lavender;\" colspan=\"7\" | Helicopters (209)\n|-\n|[[Boeing AH-64 Apache]]\n|[[File:AH-64E Apache-Guardian-0006.jpg|200x200px]]\n|{{Flagu|USA}}\n|[[Attack helicopter]]\n|AH-64E\n|0 <!-- In September 2019, eight apaches were inducted in the Air Force (NOT Army) -->\n|'''Status: On order'''\n6 aircraft on order. To be delivered starting 2023.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/defence/india-us-sign-contract-for-additional-apache-attack-choppers/articleshow/74299279.cms|title=India, US sign contract for additional Apache attack choppers|date=2020-02-25|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[HAL Light Combat Helicopter]]\n|[[File:HAL LCH at Aero india 2013.JPG|200x200px]]\n|{{IND}}\n|[[Attack helicopter]]\n|LCH\n|\n|'''Status: Production Started'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/current-affairs/arun-jaitley-inaugurates-manufacture-of-light-combat-helicopter-at-hal-117082600691_1.html|title=Arun Jaitley inaugurates manufacture of light combat helicopter at HAL|date=27 August 2017|accessdate=21 December 2017}}</ref><br>5 LCH to be procured under LSP.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/hal-gets-order-for-15-light-combat-helicopters/article22260545.ece|title=HAL gets order for 15 Light Combat Helicopters|date=22 December 2017|accessdate=25 December 2017}}</ref> Total 114 on order.<ref name=\"Flightglobal\" /> It has completed all initial tests. Trials of missile firing were held in mid 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.indiandefensenews.in/2016/03/hals-lch-passes-rocket-trials-will.html|title=HAL'S LCH PASSES ROCKET TRIALS|last=|first=|date=2016-03-16|website=INDIANDEFENSE NEWS|publisher=INDIANDEFENSE NEWS|access-date=}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[HAL Rudra]] || [[File:HAL Rudra at Aero India 2013.JPG|200px]] || {{IND}} || [[Attack helicopter]] || ALH-WSI || 50 || 50 in service with 10 more on order<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/nation/2019/oct/08/army-boosting-combat-fighting-capabilities-with-major-inductions-of-indigenous-helicopters-2044607.html|title=Army boosting combat fighting capabilities with major inductions of indigenous helicopters|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2020-03-01}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[HAL Dhruv]] || [[File:IA-1136 HAL Dhruv (Indian Army).jpg|200px]] || {{IND}} || [[Utility helicopter]] ||  || 145<ref name=\"Flightglobal\"/> || Total of 264 on order.<ref name=\"Flightglobal\"/>\n|-\n|[[Kamov Ka-226]]\n|[[File:Kamov Ka-226 MAKS 2005.jpg|200x200px]]\n|{{Flagu|India}}<br>{{Flagu|Russia}}\n|[[Utility helicopter]]\n|Ka-226T\n|\n| 200 to be built in India at HAL Helicopter Manufacturing plant being built at Tumkuru.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.indiandefensenews.in/2015/08/make-in-india-russia-wants-co.html|title=MAKE IN INDIA: RUSSIA WANTS CO-PRODUCTION OF KA-226 CHOPPERS TO START AS SOON AS POSSIBLE|last=|first=|date=2015-08-29|website=INDIANDEFENSE NEWS|publisher=INDIANDEFENSE NEWS|access-date=}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[HAL Light Utility Helicopter]]\n|[[File:HAL - Light Utility Helicopter (LUH).jpg|200x200px]]\n|{{IND}}\n|[[Utility helicopter|Utility helicopter /]] [[Observation helicopter|Observation Helicopter]]\n|LUH\n|\n|'''Status: Under Development/Undergoing Trials'''<br>First flight held on September 6, 2016.126 0rdered for the army out of 187 to be produced <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.flightglobal.com/news/articles/pictures-indias-light-utility-helicopter-has-maid-429093/|title=India\u2019s Light Utility Helicopter has maiden flight|last=|first=|date=7 September 2016|website=FLIGHTGLOBAL.COM|publisher=FLIGHTGLOBAL.COM|access-date=}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[A\u00e9rospatiale SA 315B Lama|HAL Cheetah, Cheetal & Lancer]] || [[File:Indian Army's HAL Cheetah at Leh cropped.JPG|200px]] || {{IND}} || [[Utility helicopter]]<hr>[[Utility helicopter]]<hr>[[Counter-insurgency]] || Cheetah<hr>Cheetal<hr>Lancer || 23<ref name=\"Flightglobal\"/><hr>4<ref name=\"Flightglobal\"/><hr>12 || In service.<ref name=\"Flightglobal\"/> They are expected to be replaced by Kamov 226T Helicopters in near future and there after by indigenously being developed HAL Light Utility Helicopter.\n|-\n| [[A\u00e9rospatiale Alouette III#India|HAL Chetak & Chetan]] || [[File:Z395 Aerospatiale Alouette III Indian Air Force (8448378722).jpg|200px]] || {{IND}} || [[Utility helicopter]] || Chetak || 4<ref name=\"Flightglobal\"/> || Licence-built A\u00e9rospatiale Alouette III. Being withdrawn from service and replaced by [[HAL Dhruv]]. \n|}\n\n===UAVs===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Aircraft\n!Photo\n!Origin\n!Role\n!Version\n!Number\n!Comment\n|-\n| [[IAI Heron]] || [[File:Salon du Bourget 20090619 075.jpg|170px]] || {{Flagu|Israel}} || [[Unmanned aerial vehicle]] ||  || 50+ || \n|-\n| [[IAI Searcher]] || [[File:Pair of IN Searcher UAVs.JPG|170px]] || {{ISR}} || [[Unmanned aerial vehicle]] || Searcher II<br>Searcher I  || 120+\n|\n|-\n| [[IAI Harpy]]    || [[File:Paris Air Show 2007-06-24 n25.jpg|170px]]  || {{Flagu|Israel}} || [[Unmanned combat aerial vehicle]] || || 40 ||\n|-\n| [[IAI Harop]]    || [[File:IAI Harop PAS 2013 01.jpg|170px]]  || {{Flagu|Israel}} || [[Unmanned combat aerial vehicle]] || || 110+<ref>https://www.debka.com/mivzak/indian-air-force-buys-another-54-israeli-harop-drones/</ref> || 54 more on order \n|-\n|[[DRDO Rustom|DRDO Rustom 2]]||[[File:DRDO Rustom.JPG|170px]] ||{{Flagu|India}}|| [[Unmanned combat aerial vehicle]] || || ||'''Status: Under Development/Undergoing Trials.''' First flight held on November 16, 2016.\n|}\n\n==Radar==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:90%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Name \n!Image\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Type \n! style=\"width:5%;\"| Quantity \n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Origin \n! Notes\n|-\n| [[Rajendra Radar|Rajendra]] \n|[[File:Rajendra Radar by BEL image.jpg|center|frameless]]||[[Passive electronically scanned array|Passive electronically scanned array radar]] ||  || {{Flagu|India}} || '''Status:''' Inducted  .\n|-\n|[[Indian Doppler Radar|INDRA]]\n|[[File:Sri Lanka Military 0257.jpg|cente|frameless]]\n|[[Passive electronically scanned array|Passive electronically scanned array radar]]\n|\n|{{Flagu|India}}\n|'''Status:''' Inducted  .\n|-\n|[[Swathi Weapon Locating Radar]]\n|[[File:WLR Mockup.jpg|cente|frameless]]\n|[[Artillery locating radar|Artillery Locating Radar]]\n|\n|{{Flagu|India}}\n|'''Status:''' Inducted  .\n|-\n|[[Central acquisition radar (3D-CAR)|Rohini]]\n|[[File:Rohini radar at 2010 Republic Day Parade.jpg|cente|frameless]]\n|[[3D radar]]\n|\n|{{Flagu|India}}\n|'''Status:''' Inducted  .\n|-\n|[[Samyukta Electronic Warfare System|Samyukta]]\n|\n|[[Electronic warfare|Electronic Warfare]]\n|\n|{{Flagu|India}}\n|'''Status:''' Inducted  .\n|-\n|Bharani\n|\n|Low Level Light weight 2D Radar\n|\n|{{Flagu|India}}\n|'''Status:''' Inducted  .\n|-\n|Multi Mission Radar\n|\n|Multi Mission Radar\n|\n|{{Flagu|India}}\n|'''Status:''' Development .\n|-\n|Short Range Battle Field Surveillance Radar\n|\n|Short Range [[Battlefield surveillance radar|Battle Field Surveillance Radar]] \n|\n|{{Flagu|India}}\n|'''Status:''' Inducted  .\n|-\n|[[Radar imaging|Through wall detection Radar]]\n|\n|[[Radar imaging|Through wall detection Radar]]\n|\n|{{Flagu|India}}\n|'''Status:''' Development . Prototype ready.\n|-\n|[[Ground-penetrating radar|Ground Penetration Radar]]\n|\n|[[Ground-penetrating radar|Ground Penetration Radar]]\n|\n|{{Flagu|India}}\n|'''Status:''' Development . Prototype ready.\n|}\n\n==Future procurements==\n\n===Vehicles===\n* BMP-2 based AKASH SAM carrier production started at [[Ordnance Factory Medak]].\n* BMP-2 based NBC protected recon vehicle to be manufactured at [[Ordnance Factory Medak]].\n* Light Specialist Vehicle \u2013 LSV with mounting provision for MMG to be purchased by Infantry division.\n* Indian Army has shown interest in TATA LAMV(Light Armoured Multipurpose Vehicle) with mounting provision of MMG, BFSR, HHTI to be purchased by Mechanized Forces. It is slated to be future ready for Battlefield Management System (BMS).\n* Future Infantry Combat Vehicle - 2600 FICV to be procured to replace old BMP-2s. Initially, GoI asked different private and public sector companies to delevelop FICV. But, it seems that the plan to develop new vehicle is put on hold due to budgetary cuts. Instead, upgradation of old BMP-2s with new powerful engines, transmission and new [[Kliver turret]] with 30mm gun and four [[Kornet-M]] ATGM launchers in being tried.\n* [[Armoured Personnel Carrier]] - 100 APC to be procured for United Nations peace keeping missions.\n* 1586 vehicles to be procured to mount ATGMs on these.\n* 1770 Future Ready Combat Vehicle to replace the T-72 MBT's. The tanks would have 120/125mm smooth bore gun, be in medium weight class (50 tonnes) with a crew of 3/4 personnel.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianarmy.nic.in/writereaddata/RFI/542/RFI%20FRCV%2008%20Nov%2017.pdf|title=Indian Army FRCV RFI|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n===Artillery and missile systems===\nUnder the Field Artillery Rationalization Plan, Indian Army plans to procure 3000 to 4000 155&nbsp;mm towed, wheeled and tracked artillery systems.{{citation needed|date=April 2012}} The requirement for artillery guns to be met with indigenous development and production.<ref>{{cite web |author=Business Standard |url=http://www.business-standard.com/india/news/155-mm-gun-contract-drdo-entersfray/402834/ |title=155-mm gun contract: DRDO enters the fray |publisher=Business-standard.com |date= |accessdate=2012-04-21}}</ref> Production of crucial bi-modular charge system will be started soon at Nalanda ordnance factory. HEMRL, a DRDO lab has developed the technology indigenously.<ref>{{cite web |author=the hindu businessline |url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/industry-and.../article3342018.ece |title=Nalanda Ordnance Factory Board developing indigenous artillery shells |publisher=the hindu.com |date= |accessdate=2012-05-13 }}{{dead link|date=September 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n* State-run Ordnance Factory Board (OFB) will deliver two types of indigenously developed 155mm howitzers to the Indian Army based on the [[FH 77|FH77B]] howitzer purchased way back in 1986. One version will be 155/39 calibre while the other will be 155/45 calibre. Trials are to be completed by June 2013\n*<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.army-technology.com/news/newsindian-ofb-soon-deliver-artillery-guns-user-trials |title=Indian OFB soon to deliver artillery guns for user trials |publisher=Army Technology |date= |accessdate=2013-08-23}}</ref> Government is also evaluating 155mm/52 self-propelled howitzers wherein three Indian vendors, including two private sector companies, have been selected for trials of their equipment. \n*[[Agni missile system|Agni-V]] \u2013 Intercontinental version of the Agni missile system. The missile was test fired for the first time on 19 April 2012 and was inducted in 2014.\n*[[Bharat Dynamics|Bharat Dynamics Limited]] has tested Second Generation Amogha [[anti-tank missile]]s with a range of 2.8&nbsp;km(Tested).This [[anti-tank missile]] will be handed to the Indian Army after some trials.\n*[[Defence Research and Development Organisation|DRDO]] will start working on [[Man-portable anti-tank systems|Man portable]] [[Nag (missile)|Nag]] [[Anti-tank missile|anti tank missile]].\n\n===Infantry equipment===\n\n*AK-203 - 750,000 rifles to be manufactured locally by OFB. It will be the standard weapon of Indian Army replacing INSAS, expected follow on orders from paramilitary and state police.\n*Caracal International CAR 816 - Order placed for 94,000 units of CAR 816 carbine.\n*[[Modern Sub Machine Carbine]] - to replace the Indian [[Sterling submachine gun]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.defenseworld.net/go/defensenews.jsp?id=4106 |title=DRDO to display sub-machine carbine at Defexpo 2010 |publisher=Defenseworld.net |accessdate=2012-04-21 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110723085406/http://www.defenseworld.net/go/defensenews.jsp?id=4106 |archivedate=23 July 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n*Indian Army has requirement for 300,000 modular body armour and ballistic helmets primarily for their Infantry regiments. RFI's have been issued.\n*1000 Anti materiel rifles are to acquired for which global RFI's have been issued by the MOD.\n* [[Sniper Rifles]] - 5000 new sniper rifles in [[.338 Lapua Magnum]] to be procured to replace old [[Dragunov SVD]]s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiatimes.com/news/india/indian-army-looking-for-a-deadlier-sniper-rifle-to-replace-ageing-draganov-266996.html |title=Indian Army Looking For A Deadlier Sniper Rifle To Replace Ageing Draganov |publisher=Indiatimes|date=8 December 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Ballistic helmet]]-Indian army has ordered about 158,000 (1.58 Lakh) ballistic helmets from Kanpur-based defence firm [[MKU (company)|MKU]]. The Indian Government has approved procurement of 328,000 (3.28 Lakh) ballistic helmets.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/defence/army-gets-the-first-lot-of-7500-hi-tech-helmets/articleshow/59585896.cms|title=Army gets the first lot of 7,500 hi-tech helmets|last=Gurung|first=Shaurya Karanbir|date=2018-07-13|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2019-07-09}}</ref>\n*[[Bulletproof vest]]-The Ministry of Defence ordered 186,138 (1.86 Lakh) bulletproof vests on April 9, 2018. These will be manufactured in India by SMPP Pvt Ltd. This is in addition to the 50,000 vests ordered in 2016 under emergency procurement.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/army-bulletproof-jackets-make-in-india-1208531-2018-04-09|title=Army soldiers get 1.86 lakh new bulletproof jackets after 9-year wait|date=9 April 2018|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2019-07-09}}</ref>\n\n===Aviation===\n* '''Light Utility Helicopter''': The Indian army has projected a requirement for up to 197 light helicopters to replace its ageing fleet of [[A\u00e9rospatiale Alouette III|Chetaks]] and [[A\u00e9rospatiale Alouette II|Cheetahs]]. The Indian Army chose [[Eurocopter Fennec|Eurocopter AS 550]] under a US$550 million contract in summer of 2007. Under this contract 60 helicopters were to be supplied from Eurocopter in fly-away condition and the rest were to be assembled by HAL in India. This order was later scrapped due to allegations of unfair field trials from one of the competing company, Bell Helicopters.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaenews.com/india/20071206/84767.htm |title=Indian Army tender for 197 Eurocopter Fennec helicopters Scrapped |publisher=Indiaenews.com |date=6 December 2007 |accessdate=2012-04-21}}</ref><ref>[http://www.indiaprwire.com/businessnews/20070408/21846.htm Eurocopter wins big Indian Army deal] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070615212045/http://www.indiaprwire.com/businessnews/20070408/21846.htm |date=15 June 2007 }}</ref> A fresh tender process was initiated later in which [[Eurocopter Fennec]] and [[Kamov Ka-226]] were shortlisted for user trials. Trials were completed and [[Kamov Ka-226]] was declared winner and about 200 helicopters are to be made in India under the \"[[Make in India]]\" initiative, Indian Army have planned to replace obsolete [[A\u00e9rospatiale Alouette III|Chetaks]] and [[A\u00e9rospatiale Alouette II|Cheetahs]] with it, until the arrival of [[HAL Light Utility Helicopter|HAL LUH]], as the later would be ready for its first flight only by 2017.\n* '''HAL Light Combat Helicopter''' - HAL has obtained a firm order to deliver 114 HAL Light Combat Helicopters to the Indian Army.<ref>Shenoy, Ramnath. [http://www.ptinews.com/news/422197_India-to-test-fly-light-combat-helicopters-shortly \"India to test fly light combat helicopters shortly\"]. [[Press Trust of India]], 14 December 2009. Retrieved 4 January 2010. {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091218083937/http://www.ptinews.com/news/422197_India-to-test-fly-light-combat-helicopters-shortly |date=18 December 2009 }}</ref>\n* '''Boeing AH-64 Apache''' - The [[Government of India]] approved the purchase of 6 helicopters in August 2017.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://m-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org/c/m.ndtv.com/india-news/army-to-get-its-first-attack-helicopters-apache-deal-worth-655-million-1738867?amp=1&akamai-rum=off |title=For First Time, Army To Get Its Own Attack Helicopters, Boeing Apaches |website=NDTV |date= |access-date=2017-08-17}}</ref><ref>[http://defencenews.in/article/Indian-Army-asked-for-11-Apaches,-but-got-only-6-283793 ] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170824081539/http://www.defencenews.in/article/Indian-Army-asked-for-11-Apaches,-but-got-only-6-283793 |date=24 August 2017 }}. Defense News</ref>\n\n==Gallery==\n[[File:TATA LPTA 1615 TC.jpg|none|thumb|TATA LPTA 1615 on board freight train at Surat railway station]]\n\n<gallery>\nFile:IA Artillery.jpg|[[Indian Army]] [[artillery]] gun\nFile:India army SwarajT3500 2007 front.JPG|[[Indian Army]] Ambulance\nFile:BFSR-SR with thermal imager.JPG|[[Bharat Electronics|BEL]] Battlefield Surveillance Radar-Short Range ([[BFSR-SR]])\nFile:T-90 firing.jpg|[[T-90]] tanks during firing in [[Thar Desert]].\nFile:Soldier Sikh LI INF of the Indian Army practices aim during MALABAR 2006.jpg|A soldier tests a [[Beretta 92]].\nFile:Indian Army T-72 image 2.jpg|[[Indian Army]] [[T-72]] with ERA\nFile:Indian Army Armoured Corps.jpg|[[Indian Army]] Armoured Corps during a [[training]] exercise\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Currently active military equipment by country]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Indian Army}}\n{{Military of India}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Equipment Of The Indian Army}}\n[[Category:Indian Army]]\n[[Category:Military equipment of India]]\n", "text_old": "{{more citations needed|date=January 2014}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=April 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2013}}\n\nThis is a list of some of the modern and historical '''equipment used by the [[Indian Army]]'''. Most of the army equipment is of foreign design and produced under licence in India but efforts are on to progressively design and manufacture equipment locally. The 41 [[Indian Ordnance Factories]] under control of [[Ordnance Factories Board]] manufacture most of the Army equipment like [[small arms]], [[ammunition]], [[combat vehicle]]s, [[artillery]], [[tank]]s etc.\n\n==Infantry weapons==\n\n===Small Arms===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|+\n|-\n! style=\"width:15%;\" | Name\n! style=\"width:10%;\" | Weapon\n! style=\"width:15%;\" | Type\n! style=\"width:5%;\" | Caliber\n! style=\"width:10%;\" | Origin\n! Notes\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" |Handguns\n|-\n|[[Pistol Auto 9mm 1A]]\n|[[File:Pistol Auto 9 mm 1A - Kolkata 2012-01-23 8779.JPG|[[Pistol Auto 9mm 1A]]|150px]]||[[Semi-automatic pistol]]||[[9mm Parabellum|9\u00d719mm Parabellum]]||{{CAN}}<br>{{IND}}||'''Status: In service.''' Standard side-arm of the Indian Army, manufactured under license.\n|-\n|[[Glock 17]]\n|[[File:Glock17.jpg|Glock 17|150px]]||[[Semi-automatic pistol]]||[[9mm Parabellum|9\u00d719mm Parabellum]]||{{AUT}}||'''Status: In service.''' Standard Special Forces pistol.\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" |Shotgun\n|-\n|[[Franchi SPAS-15]]\n|[[File:SPAS15.jpg|Franchi SPAS-15 Combat Shotgun|150px]]||[[Combat Shotgun]]|| 18.5 x 76&nbsp;mm NATO ||{{ITA}}||'''Status: In service.''' Used by special forces, which includes NSG.\n|-\n|[[OFB pump action Shotgun]]\n|[[File:6--sa12pagun.jpg|150px]]\n|[[pump action]]\n|[[12-gauge shotgun]]\n|{{IND}}\n|'''Status:In Service'''\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" |SMGs\n|-\n|[[Sterling submachine gun|SAF Carbine 2A1]]\n|[[File:Sterling SMG.JPG|[[SAF Carbine 2A1]]|150px]]||[[Submachine gun]]||[[9mm Parabellum|9\u00d719mm Parabellum]]||{{IND}}<br>{{GBR}}||'''Status: In service/will be Replaced.''' [[submachine gun|SAF Carbine 1A]]. To be replaced by the [[Modern Sub Machine Carbine|MSMC]].\n|-\n|[[Uzi#Military variants|Micro-Uzi]]\n|[[File:Uzi of the israeli armed forces.jpg|Micro-Uzi|150px]]||[[Submachine gun]]||[[9\u00d719mm Parabellum]]||{{ISR}}||'''Status: In service.''' For use by Special Forces. Micro-Uzi variant used.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bharat-rakshak.com/LAND-FORCES/Army/Galleries/50-5/0548.jpg |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-11-11 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121010190951/http://www.bharat-rakshak.com/LAND-FORCES/Army/Galleries/50-5/0548.jpg |archivedate=10 October 2012 |df=dmy-all }}?</ref>\n|-\n|[[Heckler & Koch MP5]]\n|[[File:Heckler & Koch MP5-1.jpg|MP5 Submachine Gun|150px]]||[[Submachine gun]]||[[9\u00d719mm Parabellum]]||{{GER}}||'''Status: In service.''' Used by Indian Army Special Forces\n|-\n|[[Br\u00fcgger & Thomet MP9]]\n|[[File:B&T MP9 SMG.JPG|MP9 machine pistol|150px]]||[[Machine pistol]]||[[9\u00d719mm Parabellum]]||{{CHE}}||'''Status: In service.''' Used by [[Ghatak Force|Ghatak Platoon]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2012/20121112/main4.htm|title=The Tribune, Chandigarh, India - Main News|website=www.tribuneindia.com|access-date=2016-10-27}}</ref>\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" |Assault Rifles\n|-\n|[[Steyr AUG]]\n|[[File:Steyr-AUG.jpeg|150px]]\n|[[Assault Rifle|Assault Rifle/Sub Machine Gun]]\n|[[5.56\u00d745mm NATO]] and [[9\u00d719mm Parabellum]](SMG Variant)\n|{{AUT}}\n|'''Status: In service.''' Used by special forces in small numbers.\n|-\n|[[FN SCAR]]\n|[[File:Scar L Standard.jpg|150px]]\n|[[Assault rifle]]\n|[[5.56\u00d745mm NATO]] and [[7.62\u00d751mm NATO|7.62x51mm NATO]]\n|{{BEL}}\n|'''Status: In service.''' Used by special forces including NSG, Para SF, MARCOS and SFF.\n|-\n||[[IMI Galil|IMI GALIL]]\n|[[File:Imfdb galil.jpg|150px]]\n|[[Assault rifle]]\n|[[5.56\u00d745mm NATO]]\n|{{ISR}}\n|'''Status: In service.''' Small numbers used by Para SF.\n|-\n|[[IMI Tavor TAR-21]]\n|[[File:IWI-Tavor-TAR-21w1.jpg|IMI Tavor|150px]]||[[Assault rifle]]||[[5.56\u00d745mm NATO]]||{{ISR}}||'''Status: In service.''' Standard Special Forces assault rifle.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.defenseindustrydaily.com/2007/02/tavor21-rifle-headed-into-service-with-indian-special-forces/index.php#more|title=Tavor21 rifle headed into service with Indian Special Forces|publisher=DefenseIndustryDaily.com|access-date=27 July 2007|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070601183316/http://www.defenseindustrydaily.com/2007/02/tavor21-rifle-headed-into-service-with-indian-special-forces/index.php#more|archive-date=1 June 2007|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://mod.nic.in/product&supp/welcome.html |title=Ministry of Defence, Govt of India |publisher=Mod.nic.in |accessdate=2012-04-21 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120704170459/http://mod.nic.in/product%26supp/welcome.html |archivedate=4 July 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n|[[AKM]]\n|[[File:AKM automatkarbin - 7,62x39mm.jpg|AKM Assault Rifle|150px]]||[[Assault rifle]]||[[7.62\u00d739mm]]||{{USSR}}||'''Status: In service.''' Used by the Army.\n|-\n|[[AR-M1]]\n|[[File:Arsenalakimage.jpg|thumb]]||[[Assault rifle]]||[[7.62\u00d739mm]]||{{BUL}}||'''Status: In service.''' Used by the Army.\n|-\n|[[Vz. 58]]\n|[[File:Vz58-JH01.jpg|150px]]\n|[[Assault rifle]]\n|[[7.62\u00d739mm]]\n|{{CZS}}\n|'''Status: In service.''' Used by the army in small numbers.\n|-\n|[[German military rifles|Mpi-KmS 72]]\n|[[File:MPi-Km 72.jpg|alt=|center|frameless|220x220px]]\n\n|[[Assault rifle]]\n|[[7.62\u00d739mm]]\n|{{flag|East Germany}}\n|'''Status: In Service''' Used by the army in small amount \n|-\n|[[AK-103]]\n|[[File:AK-103 Assault Rifle.JPG|AK-103 Assault Rifle|150px]]||[[Assault rifle]]||[[7.62\u00d739mm]]||{{RUS}}||'''Status: In service.''' Used by the Indian Police, Army, Paramilitary including special forces MARCOS, Garud, Ghatak, and NSG.\n|-\n|[[AK-100 (rifle family)#AK-100M/200 Series|AK-203]]\n|\n|[[Assault Rifle]]\n|[[7.62\u00d739mm]]\n|{{RUS}}{{IND}}\n|'''Status: On Order.'''\nWill be the standard weapon of Indian Army. 750,000 rifles to be manufactured locally by OFB. Till now final Production Variant design haven't been finalized yet due to cost increase than expected initially. Expected follow on orders from paramilitary and state police.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/made-in-amethi-ak-203s-to-give-forces-edge-in-fight-against-terror-pm-modi/articleshow/68243351.cms|title='Made in Amethi' AK-203s to give security forces edge in fight against terror: PM Modi {{!}} India News - Times of India|date=March 3, 2019|newspaper=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2019-07-09|agency=Ist}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Fab Defense Mod. AKMS]]\n|[[File:44844FAB.jpg|thumb]]\n|[[Assault rifle]]\n|[[7.62\u00d739 mm]] \n|{{ISR}}\n|'''Status: In Service'''\nPresent in large amount. Extensively used by all units.\n|-\n|[[SIG Sauer SIG516#Variants|SIG-716 Patrol G2]]\n|[[File:SIG SG 516 14.5\u2033.jpg|150px]]\n|[[Battle Rifle]]\n|[[7.62\u00d751mm NATO|7.62x51mm]]\n|{{USA}}\n|'''Status: In Service.'''\nTotal Order placed for 72,400 units of SIG-716 Patrol G2 model.\n10,000 received by Early 2020 and have been included in service.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/sig-sauer-deal-indian-army-72000-rifles-rs-700-crore-1454371-2019-02-12|title=Govt signs mega Rs 700-crore deal to buy 72,000 modern rifles for Indian Army|date=February 12, 2019|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2019-07-09}}</ref> Deliveries started in December 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/defence/indian-army-gets-new-american-assault-rifles-in-kashmir-valley-against-terrorists-pakistan-army-on-loc/articleshow/72467643.cms|title=Indian Army gets new American assault rifles in Kashmir Valley against terrorists, Pakistan Army on LoC|date=December 11, 2019|website=[[Asian News International]]|via=[[The Economic Times]]|language=en|access-date=2019-12-11}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[CAR 816|Caracal International CAR 816]]\n|[[File:CAR 816.jpg|CAR 816|150px]]\n|[[Carbine]]\n|[[5.56\u00d745mm NATO]]\n|{{UAE}}\n|'''Status: On Order.'''\nOrder placed for 94,000 units of CAR 816 carbine.\n|-\n|[[T91 assault rifle]]\n|[[File:T91 assault rifle.jpg|150px]]\n|[[Assault rifle]]\n|[[5.56\u00d745mm NATO]]\n|{{TWN}}\n|'''Status: In Service.''' 1000+ unit of this rifle were brought\n|-\n|[[M16 rifle]]\n|[[File:M16a1m16a2m4m16a45wi.jpg|frameless|146x146px]]\n|[[Assault rifle]]\n|[[5.56\u00d745mm NATO]]\n|{{USA}}\n|'''Status: In service.''' Used by special forces\n|-\n|[[M4 carbine|M4A1 Carbine]]\n|[[File:PEO M4 Carbine RAS M68 CCO.jpg|M4A1 Assault Rifle|150px]]||[[Assault rifle]]||[[5.56\u00d745mm NATO]]||{{USA}}||'''Status: In service.''' Used by special forces, including PARA SF and Ghatak SF and MARCOS.\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" |Sniper rifles\n|-\n|[[Steyr SSG 69]]\n|[[File:Steyr SSG 69.jpg|Sniper Rifle|150px]]||[[Sniper rifle]]|| 7.62\u00d751mm NATO ||{{AUT}}||'''Status: In service.''' Standard bolt-action sniper rifle.\n|-\n|[[Mauser|Mauser SP66]]\n|[[File:Mauser sp66.JPG|Sniper Rifle|150px]]||[[Sniper rifle]]|| 7.62\u00d751mm NATO ||{{GER}}||'''Status: In service.''' Standard bolt-action sniper rifle.\n|-\n|[[SIG Sauer SSG 3000]]\n|[[File:SIG Sauer SSG 3000.jpg|Sniper Rifle|150px]]||[[Sniper rifle]]|| 7.62\u00d751mm NATO ||{{GER}}||'''Status: In service.''' Standard bolt-action sniper rifle.\n|-\n|[[Dragunov Sniper Rifle|Dragunov SVD]]\n|[[File:SVD Dragunov.jpg|Dargunov Sniper Rifle|150px]]||[[Sniper rifle]]||[[7.62\u00d754mmR]]||{{USSR}}<br>{{IND}}||'''Status: In service.''' Standard Designated Marksman rifle(DMR). To be replaced by a 7.62mm NATO DMR under the Army modernisation plan.<ref name=\"ndtv.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ndtv.com/india-news/re-arming-the-indian-armys-troops-with-lethal-modern-weapons-505844|title=Re-arming the Indian Army's troops with lethal, modern weapons|author=Nitin Gokhale|date=28 November 2012|work=NDTV.com|accessdate=4 April 2016}}</ref>\n|