hermobaric missiles and two tandem warhead Konkurs missiles. It also has an integrated TI sight, an LRF, and has an AGL mounted on the turret which is also stabilised in the horizontal plane. 100 added each year. To enhance the rate to 125 a year.<ref name=\"Indian Army: Armoured Fighting Vehicles\"/> Currently ~2500 are in active service.<ref name=\"Indian Army: Armoured Fighting Vehicles\">{{cite web|url=http://www.bharat-rakshak.com/LAND-FORCES/Equipment/Armour/346-BMP-2.html |title=Land Forces Site \u2013 BMP-2 |publisher=Bharat Rakshak |date=20 February 2002 |accessdate=2012-04-21 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121007005545/http://www.bharat-rakshak.com/LAND-FORCES/Equipment/Armour/346-BMP-2.html |archivedate=7 October 2012 |df=dmy }}</ref> Manufactured locally in India by [[Ordnance Factory Medak]].  All BMP-2/2K vehicles are to be upgraded to BMP-2M standard.<ref>[http://www.deagel.com/news/Indian-Army-to-Upgrade-its-BMP-22K-Infantry-Combat-Vehicles-to-BMP-2M-Standard_n000011456.aspx Indian Army to Upgrade its BMP-2/2K Infantry Combat Vehicles to BMP-2M Standard] - Deagel.com, 6 May 2013</ref>\n|-\n|'''[[Abhay IFV]]'''\n|\n|[[Infantry fighting vehicle]]\n|\n|{{Flagu|India}}\n|Status:approx 2600 planned to replace the old bmp-2\n|-\n! colspan=\"6\" style=\"align: center;\" | [[Armoured Personnel Carrier]]s\n|-\n| [[BTR-50]] || [[File:BTR-50-latrun-1-2.jpg|200x200px]] \n|[[Armoured Personnel Carrier]]||100+ || {{USSR}} || Status: Total 200 in service.\n|-\n| [[TATA Kestrel]] ||<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Tata Kestrel.jpg|frameless]] -->\n|[[Armoured personnel carrier]]\n|\n|{{Flag|India}}\n|Under development. Expected to be ready by 2017-18. Around 1000+ planned<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.indiandefensenews.in/2016/03/production-of-infantry-combat-vehicle.html|title=PRODUCTION OF INFANTRY COMBAT VEHICLE WILL START SIX YEARS FROM NOW: TATA MOTORS|last=|first=|date=2016-03-09|website=Indiandenfensenews|publisher=INDIANDEFENSE 