itzer]] || 25<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uniindia.com/bae-systems-to-showcase-make-in-india-m777-howitzers-at-defexpo/india/news/1868464.html|title=BAE SYSTEMS TO SHOWCASE MAKE IN INDIA M777 HOWITZERS AT DEFEXPO|date=2020-01-28|quote=To date, BAE Systems has produced and delivered 25 guns to the Indian Army, with another 70-plus planned for 2020.}}</ref> ||{{USA}} ||  '''Entering service.''' 145 ordered through FMS as of June 2016.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ndtv.com/india-news/3-decades-after-bofors-scam-indian-army-gets-first-artillery-guns-from-us-1695068|title=3 Decades After Bofors, Indian Army Gets First Artillery Guns From US|date=2017-05-18|newspaper=NDTV|access-date=2017-05-18}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Haubits FH77/A|Haubits FH77/B]] \n|[[File:Haubits 77BMK2.JPG|200x200px]]|| [[Howitzer]] || 410<ref name=didmcfi>{{cite web|title=Murky Competitions for Indian Howitzer Orders May End Soon\u2026 Or Not|url=http://www.defenseindustrydaily.com/murky-competition-for-2b-india-howitzer-order-may-end-soon-0805/|accessdate=2013-02-21}}</ref> || {{SWE}} || '''In service/Being replaced.''' 155&nbsp;mm gun made by Bofors. 410 acquired from 1986\u20131991. To be replaced in near future by [[Dhanush howitzer|Dhanush Howitzer]].\n|-\n| [[130 mm towed field gun M1954 (M-46)|M-46]]\n|[[File:M-46 Lutsk.jpg|200x200px]]|| [[Howitzer]] || 900 || {{USSR}}<br>{{ISR}} || '''In service.''' 180 M-46 130&nbsp;mm howitzer guns upgraded to 155&nbsp;mm standard by [[Soltam]] and 300 to be upgraded by OFB.<ref name=M46Upgrade155>{{cite news|title=In a first, pvt Indian firms can bid to make artillery guns|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/in-a-first-pvt-indian-firms-can-bid-to-make-artillery-guns/1101211/|accessdate=13 May 2013|newspaper=The Indian Express|date=12 April 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://defence.pk/threads/indian-army-and-its-old-weapons-and-equipments.215631/page-2|title=Indian Army and its old Weapons and Equipments|work=Pakistan Defence|accessdate=4 April 2016}}<